'''René Rachou''' was a [[Brazil]]ian [[physician]] and [[research]]er on [[malaria]] who was the director of the Institute of Malariology of the [[Oswaldo Cruz Institute]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]]. He also worked with the [[Pan-American Health Organization]].<ref>http://www.cpqrr.fiocruz.br/pg/en/about-us/history/ 1957 entry</ref> The Institute was moved to [[Belo Horizonte]] in 1955, and, after his death, in 1965, it was renamed Centro de Pesquisas René Rachou in his honor.<ref>http://www.cpqrr.fiocruz.br/pg/en/about-us/history/ 1966 entry</ref>

